item.description:
@Adobe wrote:

you need to either, update your java version on: http://www.oracle.com/technetwork/java/javase/downloads/index.html

Or enable something on your firewall. I’ve had it happen to me when i used google chrome, there used to be something on the top such as: “run this time” or “update plugins” if you click"run this time" it usually works for me.
